# Estate Orchestrator — Cursor Rules
# These rules apply to every file in this project.
# Cursor's AI reads these automatically. Do not delete this file.

## What this project is
This is the Estate Operating System boundary orchestrator for MH.
It enforces security boundaries between vault layers.
It operates on markdown files with YAML frontmatter.

## The golden rules — never break these
1. All scripts must default to DRY-RUN mode. Nothing moves, writes, or deletes without an explicit --confirm flag.
2. Every script must print plain-English output describing exactly what it did or would do.
3. Scripts must never touch files outside their explicitly designated input/output directories.
4. Every script must exit with a clear error message if anything goes wrong. Never fail silently.
5. Never modify vault files except through the designated behavior functions.
6. Always validate YAML frontmatter before writing. If validation fails, abort and report.
7. Every behavior must have a --test mode that runs against fake test data, not real vault files.

## Output format — every script must follow this
- DRY RUN: [action that would happen]
- ACTION: [action that was taken]
- ERROR: [what went wrong]
- PASS: [test passed]
- FAIL: [test failed]
- DONE: [summary at end of every run]

## Directory rules
- behaviors/ — one subfolder per behavior (gate, publish, health-check, backup-check, digest-generate)
- tests/ — test data and test runner scripts only
- logs/ — timestamped log files only, never delete these
- Never create files outside these directories without explicit instruction

## Language
- Python only. No PowerShell. No bash scripts.
- Python 3.10+. Standard library only unless explicitly approved.
- Every function must have a plain-English docstring.

## What this project is NOT
- Not a database. Not a web server. Not a UI.
- Not a replacement for human judgment. Every behavior requires human approval or review.
- Never connect to the internet. Never call external APIs.
